    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>National Institute on Drug Abuse (NIDA)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficacy and safety of modafinil in reducing
      cocaine use in subjects with cocaine dependence.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a double-blind, placebo-controlled, parallel group design study to evaluate the
      efficacy and safety of modafinil in reducing cocaine use in subjects with cocaine dependence.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
